510,114,20,344,512],"class_list":["post-25464","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","hentry","category-wisdom-al-hikmah","tag-agreed-upon-muttafaqun-alayhi","tag-bowing-al-ruku","tag-consensus-ijma","tag-exaltation-takbeer","tag-fiqh","tag-imam-ahmad-ibn-hanbal","tag-imam-ash-shafiee","tag-manners-adab","tag-prayer-al-salat","tag-prostration-sujud","tag-recommendation-al-mustahab"],"aioseo_notices":[],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"","jetpack_shortlink":"https:\/\/wp.me\/p95VHY-6CI","jetpack_sharing_enabled":true,"jetpack-related-posts":[{"id":25486,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/11\/30\/position-of-hands-salat\/","url_meta":{"origin":25464,"position":0},"title":"Hadith on Salat: Description of position of hands in prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"November 30, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Wa\u2019il ibn Hujr reported: He saw the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, raise his hands upon entering into prayer, exalting Allah, and Hammam described his hands as parallel to his ears. Then, the Prophet wrapped his hands in his cloak and placed his right hand over his left\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":33170,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/08\/11\/what-imam-says-in-prayer\/","url_meta":{"origin":25464,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Salat: What the Imam and followers say in prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 11, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: When the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cAllah heard those who praise him,\u201d he would say, \u201cO Allah, our Lord, for you is praise.\u201d When the Prophet bowed and raised his head, he would declare the greatness of Allah. When he stood from the\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":33168,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/08\/11\/imam-rabbana-lakal-hamd\/","url_meta":{"origin":25464,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Salat: What to say when Imam rises in prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 11, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhen the Imam says, \u2018Allah heard those who praise him,\u2019 then say, \u2018Our Lord, for you is praise.\u2019 If one\u2019s statement coincides with the statement of the angels, his previous sins will be forgiven.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":33026,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/08\/01\/prophets-dua-ruku-sujud\/","url_meta":{"origin":25464,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Salat: The Prophet&#8217;s supplication in bowing, prostration","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 1, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, would say in his bowing and prostration, \u201cGlory be to you, Allah our Lord, and your praises. Forgive me.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 4042, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 484 Grade:\u00a0Muttafaqun Alayhi\u00a0(authenticity agreed upon) according to Al-Bukhari and Muslim \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0627\u0626\u0650\u0634\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0636\u0650\u064a\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652\u0647\u064e\u0627\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25393,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/11\/09\/what-unsure-how-much-prayed\/","url_meta":{"origin":25464,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Salah: What if you forget how much you prayed?","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"November 9, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Sa\u2019id al-Khudri reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cIf one of you doubts his prayer and does not know how much he has prayed, whether three or four cycles, then let him put aside his doubt and act upon what he is certain\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":37364,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/11\/11\/dhikr-after-salat\/","url_meta":{"origin":25464,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Dhikr: Remembering Allah loudly or softly after prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"November 11, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Abbas reported: The people would raise their voices in remembrance as they left the obligatory prayers in the time of the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him. Ibn Abbas said, \u201cI used to know when they were leaving as I heard them.\u201d Sou